  "body": "### Description\n\nThe `smallrye-openapi` currently defines a set of config properties to control the generation of the `components.securitySchemes` object. E.g. `quarkus.smallrye-openapi.security-scheme-name`, `quarkus.smallrye-openapi.jwt-security-scheme-value`, and `quarkus.smallrye-openapi.jwt-bearer-format`.\r\n\r\nI could however not find any property to allow controlling the header name. What I mean is the `name` field of the \"Security Scheme Object\": https://swagger.io/specification/#security-scheme-object. It would be nice with a config property to allow controlling the value for this in the generated `openapi.yaml` file.\n\n### Implementation ideas\n\n_No response_",
